documentation.text:
@notice List all of the operators in the current registry.
 @return array containing the operator addresses.

params.shareOperatorAddress_: the address of the operator to add.

params.fundingPerOperator_: This is the per operator allocation of funds that is calculated off-chain.
params.totalFunding_: This is the total ETH sent during the call, that is appropriated for funding the operator addresses.

params.shareOperatorsAddresses_: array of operator addresses to add to the registry initially

returns._0: true if the address is a verified operator, false otherwise.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.shareOperatorAddress_: the address of the operator to remove.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

addVerifiedOperator(address).notice: Add a new verified operator to the registry.

fundOperatorAddresses(uint256,uint256).notice: Provide funds to all registered operators. The funds sent with the transaction will be evenly distributed amongst all registered operators according to per operator amount.

initialize(address[]).notice: Initialize the contract with an initial set of operator addresses.

isOperator(address).notice: Check if a given address is a verified operator in the registry.

listOperatorAddresses().notice: List all of the operators in the current registry.

removeVerifiedOperator(address).notice: Remove a verified operator from the registry.

userdoc.notice: A living canonical registry of all SHARE protocol operator EOAs (Externally Owned Accounts).
